<p>35 years after Col Baillie's death, and 17 years after the <a href="/wiki/Siege_of_Seringapatam_(1799)" title="Siege of Seringapatam (1799)">fall of Tippu Sultan</a>, Lt Col John Baillie who was his nephew, and served as the <a href="/wiki/Resident_(title)" title="Resident (title)">British Resident</a> in the Court of the <a href="/wiki/Nawab_of_Awadh" title="Nawab of Awadh">Nawab of Oudh</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lucknow" title="Lucknow">Lucknow</a>, commissioned a memorial for Col. Baillie. It is located next to the Gol Gumbaz, where Tippu Sultan is buried. It is an austere, but poignant and pretty structure.<sup id="cite_ref-DH-Mullur_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-DH-Mullur-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
